## Change Hostname of Server

- Login to Plesk control panel
- Click on **Tools & Settings** from the left side menu

```diagram

```

- Under **General Settings** click on **Server Settings**

```diagram

```

- Write your new hosting in the **Full hostname** text box

```diagram

```

- Then click on OK

## Change System Time

- Login to Plesk control panel
- Click on **Tools & Settings** from the left side menu.
- Under **General Settings** click on **System Time**

```diagram

```

- Modify system time as per you need

```diagram

```


## Change Default DNS Zone 

Whenever a new domain is added in Plesk, it uses the DNS Zone Template. You can customize this using following procedure.

- Login to Plesk control panel
- Click on **Tools & Settings** from the left side menu.
- Under **General Settings** click on **DNS Template Settings**

```diagram

```

- From the new window you can modify default DNS template values/add new record to DNS template/delete existing records etc..

```diagram

```
